Ōtsuka Kofun is located in the southern part of the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City Board|1992|p=55}}, on the north side of {{ill|Tomatsuri-yama|ja|戸祭山|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and west of the {{ill|Tagawa River (Tone River System)|ja|田川 (利根川水系)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Nearby are numerous ancient tumuli and historical sites, including {{ill|Taniguchi-yama Kofun|ja|谷口山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kitayama Kofun Cluster|ja|北山古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kawara-zuka Kofun Cluster|ja|瓦塚古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Nagaoka Hyakuana Kofun|ja|長岡百穴古墳|1=Nagaoka Hundred Caves|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. There are also remnants from the {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, such as the {{ill|Suidō-yama Tile Kiln Site|ja|水道山瓦窯跡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The {{ill|Toyosato Mahoroba Road|ja|豊郷まほろばの道|qq=draft|qq=draft}} has been developed to connect these historical locations.

To the north of Ōtsuka Kofun lies the Ōjino Kofun Cluster, consisting of several round mounds{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=107}}.

== Access ==
'''By Bus'''
* From {{ill|Utsunomiya Station|ja|宇都宮駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (JR):
** Take a {{ill|Kantō Bus|ja|関東自動車|qq=draft|qq=draft}} on the Tomatsuridai Circular Line (approx. 15 minutes). Alight at "Daini Greenhill North" and walk 10 minutes.
** Alternatively, take a bus bound for {{ill|Nikkō|ja|日光市|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and alight at "Nagaoka Kaidō Entrance," approximately 1 km via Nagaoka Kaidō{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=106}}.

'''By Car'''
* From National Route 119 ({{ill|Utsunomiya Ring Road|ja|宇都宮環状道路|qq=draft|qq=draft}}):
** Turn south at the Nagaoka-machi Intersection for 1 minute or east at the Kamitomatsuri-chō Intersection for 1 minute. Follow the branch road eastward for 1 minute to Nagaoka Kaidō.

